review_blob: Great IIPA. Resinous, apricot, grapefruit, good malt back bone as balanced as an IIPA can be. Dangerously drinkable on a hot day, warming on a cool day.

Great saison with a back splash of sour cherries. The cherries are not on front display, but rather a great accent to an incredible farmhouse ale. I am not usually a cherry fan, if not done right it seems to taste medicinal. Not the case here.
